<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
SBA is proposing to repeal its present media or opinion molder policy rule. Under the rule, as proposed, small business
concerns engaged in media activity would be eligible for SBA financial assistance unless they are otherwise ineligible
(such as businesses engaged in illegal activities or in activities that could not be funded by SBA under the Constitution,
and businesses which are not creditworthy). This action is being taken to enable SBA to promote job growth and economic
development by making SBA financial assistance available to a larger number of small business concerns.
