<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

</FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=4 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
Dun's Insight computer data base presents data from their three most recent annual industry Norms and Key Business
Ratios publications. For most industry groups, OSHA averaged data for three years. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
</FOOTNOTE>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Using a conversion formula
<FOOTCITE>12</FOOTCITE>
 based on the federal corporate tax schedule, OSHA calculated pre-tax profits from its estimate for post-tax profits.
It should be noted that the sales and profit data, while the most recent available, reflect conditions during a cyclical
trough; therefore, impacts may depict a worst case scenario. In the case of the federal government sector, price increases
for services rendered may not apply. Budgets are usually fixed (in the short run) and compliance costs are paid by reducing
funds for other items in the budget. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<FOOTNOTE>
<FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
