<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) Evaluate the need to perform alterations of the building systems to meet the minimum requirements specified
in paragraph (d) of this section in response to employee complaints of building-related illnesses; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) Take such remedial measures as the evaluation shows to be necessary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Controls for specific contaminant sources. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Tobacco smoke
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) In workplaces where the smoking of tobacco products is not prohibited, the employer shall establish designated
smoking areas and permit smoking only in such areas; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The employer shall assure that designated smoking areas are enclosed and exhausted directly to the outside,
and are maintained under negative pressure (with respect to surrounding spaces) sufficient to contain tobacco smoke
within the designated area; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The employer shall assure that cleaning and maintenance work in designated smoking areas is conducted only
when no smoking is taking place; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) The employer shall assure that employees are not required to enter designated smoking areas in the performance
of normal work activities; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) The employer shall post signs clearly indicating areas that are designated smoking areas; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) The employer shall post signs that will clearly inform anyone entering the workplace that smoking is restricted
to designated areas; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) The employer shall prohibit smoking within designated smoking areas during any period that the exhaust ventilation
system servicing that area is not properly operating. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Other indoor air contaminants
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The employer shall implement measures such as the relocation of air intakes and other pathways of building entry,
where necessary, to restrict the entry of outdoor air contaminants such as vehicle exhaust fumes, into the building;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) When general ventilation is inadequate to control air contaminants emitted from point sources within workspaces
the employer shall implement other control measures such as local source capture exhaust ventilation or substitution.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Microbial contamination
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The employer shall control microbial contamination in the building by routinely inspecting for, and promptly
repairing, water leaks that can promote growth of biologic agents; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The employer shall control microbial contamination in the building by promptly drying, replacing, removing,
or cleaning damp or wet materials; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The employer shall take measures to remove visible microbial contamination in ductwork, humidifiers, other
HVAC and building system components, or on building surfaces when found during regular or emergency maintenance
activities or during visual inspection. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Use of cleaning and maintenance chemicals, pesticides, and other hazardous chemicals in the workplace
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The employer shall assure that these chemicals are used and applied according to manufacturers' recommendations;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The employer shall inform employees working in areas to be treated with potentially hazardous chemicals, at
least within 24 hours prior to application, of the type of chemicals intended to be applied. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Air quality during renovation and remodeling
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. During renovation or remodeling, the employer shall assure that work procedures and appropriate controls are utilized
to minimize degradation of the indoor air quality of employees performing such activities and employees in other
areas of the building. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Work plan development
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Before remodeling, renovation, or similar activities are begun the employer shall meet with the contractor or
individual(s) performing the work and shall develop and implement a work plan designed to minimize entry of air contaminants
to other areas of the building during and after performance of the work; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The work plan shall consider all of the following where appropriate: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Requirements of this standard. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

